    <!-- How We Tested -->
    <section>
      <h2>How We Tested These Fiber Gummies</h2>

      <div class="tested-box">
        <h3>Our Testing Methodology</h3>
        <p>Our evaluation of fiber gummies was designed to provide actionable, evidence-based guidance that goes beyond marketing claims. Here is exactly how we arrived at our rankings:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Independent Procurement:</strong> All 25 initial products were purchased at full retail price from Amazon, Target, Walmart, Whole Foods, and brand websites. We accepted no free samples, sponsorships, or promotional considerations. Every product was bought with our own funds.</li>
          <li><strong>Fiber Type and Dose Verification:</strong> Each formula was analyzed against published clinical literature. We verified fiber source, type (soluble vs. insoluble), prebiotic classification, and whether the stated dose per serving aligned with doses used in peer-reviewed studies showing measurable benefits.</li>
          <li><strong>Third-Party Testing Audit:</strong> We verified all third-party testing claims by checking USP, NSF International, and USDA Organic databases directly. Products claiming independent testing without verifiable certifications were flagged accordingly.</li>
          <li><strong>4-Week Digestive Panel:</strong> A panel of 14 adults (ages 22-68, 8 women and 6 men) tested each product for 4 consecutive weeks. Participants tracked bowel frequency, stool consistency (Bristol Stool Scale), bloating severity, gas frequency, and overall digestive comfort using standardized daily logs.</li>
          <li><strong>Tolerance Assessment:</strong> We specifically tracked gastrointestinal side effects during the first week of use — gas, bloating, cramping, and urgency — to evaluate how well each product was tolerated by people new to fiber supplementation.</li>
          <li><strong>Taste and Compliance:</strong> Every product was rated on flavor, texture, aftertaste, and overall enjoyment on a 1-10 scale. Because fiber supplements only work when taken consistently, taste is a meaningful performance factor.</li>
          <li><strong>Value Calculation:</strong> Total cost was divided by servings and weighted against fiber dose, fiber type quality, additional nutrients, and testing certifications to calculate true per-serving value.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>Final rankings use a weighted scoring model: Fiber Quality and Dose (25%), Third-Party Testing (20%), Digestive Panel Results (25%), Tolerance (10%), Taste (10%), and Value (10%).</p>
      </div>
    </section>

