        <p>Regardless of which product you choose, remember that fiber gummies are a supplement, not a substitute. The foundation of adequate fiber intake is a diet rich in fruits, vegetables, whole grains, legumes, and nuts. Aim for 25 to 30 grams of total daily fiber from all sources, and use gummies to close whatever gap remains. Start with half the recommended serving for the first week to allow your digestive system to adjust, drink at least 8 ounces of water with your gummies, and increase gradually. Consistency over weeks, not days, is what delivers measurable digestive benefits. For a broader approach to gut health, explore our <a href="/vitamins/digestion-gummies/">digestion gummies</a> guide, which covers probiotics and enzyme-based supplements alongside fiber. And if your diet lacks <a href="/best-iron-gummies/">iron gummies</a>, they pair well with fiber for comprehensive nutritional support.</p>
